Class GUIGroupedTableColumnModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.swing.table.DefaultTableColumnModel
      • userinterface.util.GUIGroupedTableColumnModel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.beans.PropertyChangeListener, java.io.Serializable, java.util.EventListener, javax.swing.event.ListSelectionListener, javax.swing.event.TableColumnModelListener, javax.swing.table.TableColumnModel

    public class GUIGroupedTableColumnModel
extends javax.swing.table.DefaultTableColumnModel
implements javax.swing.event.TableColumnModelListener
    The TableColumnModel with the addition of Groups. A group is a set of columns. The set of columns belonging to each group are disjoint and non-empty (!).
